# MonoDesk Landing Page - Project Rules

## CSS Architecture

- **Each HTML page must have its own unique CSS file** - do not share stylesheets between pages
- CSS files should be named to match their HTML page (e.g., `bundle.html` → `css/bundle.css`)
- This allows each landing page variant to be fully independent and easily customizable

## Assets

- Assets in the `/assets` folder can be shared across all pages
- Common assets include logos, icons, and images

## File Structure

```
monodesk-landing/
├── example.html        → css/example.css
├── vibes.html          → css/vibes.css
├── bundle.html         → css/bundle.css
├── css/
│   ├── example.css     # For example.html
│   ├── vibes.css       # For vibes.html
│   └── bundle.css      # For bundle.html
└── assets/             # Shared assets
    └── logo-lockup.svg
```

## Page Titles

- Use the format `MonoDesk - [Page Name]` for all page titles
- The page name should match the HTML filename (capitalized)
- Example: `bundle.html` → `<title>MonoDesk - Bundle</title>`

## When Creating New Pages

1. Create the HTML file in the root directory
2. Create a corresponding CSS file in `/css` with the same name
3. Set the `<title>` tag to follow the format `MonoDesk - [Page Name]`
4. Link only that CSS file in the HTML `<head>`
5. Reuse assets from `/assets` as needed
6. Add the Hotjar tracking script to the `<head>` section

## Analytics Tracking

**All HTML pages must include the Hotjar tracking script** in the `<head>` section:

```html
<!-- Hotjar Tracking Code for Landing Pages -->
<script>
    (function(h,o,t,j,a,r){
        h.hj=h.hj||function(){(h.hj.q=h.hj.q||[]).push(arguments)};
        h._hjSettings={hjid:6605179,hjsv:6};
        a=o.getElementsByTagName('head')[0];
        r=o.createElement('script');r.async=1;
        r.src=t+h._hjSettings.hjid+j+h._hjSettings.hjsv;
        a.appendChild(r);
    })(window,document,'https://static.hotjar.com/c/hotjar-','.js?sv=');
</script>
```

Place this script after the CSS links and before the closing `</head>` tag.
